{"title":"USA fact of the day","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/903014021/0/marginalrevolution~USA-fact-of-the-day.html","date":1723878403000,"content":"<blockquote><p>Results show that from 2003 to 2022, average time spent at home among American adults has risen by one hour and 39 minutes in a typical day. Time at home has risen for every subset of the population and for virtually all activities. Preliminary analysis indicates that time at home is associated with lower levels of happiness and less meaning, suggesting the need for enhanced empirical attention to this major shift in the setting of American life.</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://sociologicalscience.com/articles-v11-20-553/\" target=\"_blank\">the full paper</a>, by Patrick Sharkey, via the excellent <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.nationalaffairs.com/blog/detail/findings-a-daily-roundup/lookism\" target=\"_blank\">Kevin Lewis</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/08/usa-fact-of-the-day-7.html\">USA fact of the day</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/903014021/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/903014021/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/903014021/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/903014021/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/x.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/19/903014021/margi